modules.description: Provides functions for serializing and deserializing values of type Re2.t using Bin_prot and Sexp formats, including size calculation, writing, reading, and comparison. Works with compiled regular expressions represented as Re2.t. Used to persist or transmit compiled regex patterns in a binary or s-expression format.

Provides functions for compiling regular expressions, matching patterns against strings, and extracting captured groups. Operates on strings and compiled regex patterns, supporting case-insensitive and multiline matching. Used to validate input formats, parse log lines, and filter text based on complex pattern rules.

Serializes and deserializes Re2.t values using Bin_prot and Sexp, supporting size calculation, writing, reading, and comparison. Operations include converting compiled regex patterns to and from binary or s-expression formats. Examples include saving a compiled regex to a file or transmitting it over a network. Supports efficient persistence and exchange of regular expression data.
